    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@victoriasr you should add jquery, masonry and imageloaded libraries in order to reproduce the same behaviour as in the jsFiddle. Also you're missing the base CSS style for instantsearch.\r\n\r\n```diff\r\n<!doctype html>\r\n <head>\r\n   <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\r\n+  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/instantsearch.js@2.1.1/dist/instantsearch.min.css\">\r\n   <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/instantsearch.js@2.1.1/dist/instantsearch-theme-algolia.min.css\">\r\n   <link rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\" href=\"/css/style.css\">\r\n </head>\r\n <body>\r\n \r\n <div id=\"hits\"></div>\r\n </body>\r\n </script>\r\n+  <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/g/masonry@4.2.0,jquery@3.2.1,imagesloaded@4.1.2(imagesloaded.js)\">\r\n   <script src=\"https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/instantsearch.js@2.1.1/dist/instantsearch.min.js\"></script>\r\n   <script src=\"/js/appa.js\"></script>\r\n</body>\r\n```",
